OL,3,CThousands of children referred to
OL,4,Csocial services in domestic abuse cases
OL,6,FIt comes as the Executive Office
OL,7,Fpublished a report outlining that
OL,8,Fgirls are almost three times more
OL,9,Flikely to report experiencing violence
OL,10,Fthan boys.
OL,12,FCounsellors say that education is the
OL,13,Fkey to breaking the cycle of unhealthy
OL,14,Frelationships.
OL,16,FSarah Clarke visited one West Belfast
OL,17,Fschool, where pupils are engaging in
OL,18,Fworkshops about respect, healthy
OL,19,Frelationships and social media to help
OL,20,Fbreak the cycle of abuse.
