OL,3,CThousands of children referred to
OL,4,Csocial services in domestic abuse cases
OL,6,F"Children are seen as equal victims of
OL,7,Fabuse now. The language of witnessing
OL,8,Fit or being a bystander does not
OL,9,Freally apply any more because of what
OL,10,Fwe know about how abuse, fear and
OL,11,Fdanger in the home affects children in
OL,12,Fterms of their development.
OL,14,F"When a woman is experiencing a cycle
OL,15,Fof abuse, the children are
OL,16,Fexperiencing that too.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/12
