OL,3,CThousands of children referred to
OL,4,Csocial services in domestic abuse cases
OL,6,F"That is about them in themselves but
OL,7,Fthat is also about their attachment to
OL,8,Fthe Mum who quite often is the primary
OL,9,Fcare giver. If their attachment figure
OL,10,Fis in trauma and fear and violence
OL,11,Fthen that child is in it too.
OL,13,F"So, what we know now is that trauma
OL,14,Fdeeply and profoundly affects the
OL,15,Fchild's brain in terms of development
OL,16,Fso they might experience violence,
OL,17,Fcontrol, humiliation, degradation.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/12
