OL,6,F"Some of the children have seen
OL,7,Fsiblings hurt. They have been hurt.
OL,8,FThey have seen Mum be hurt. They have
OL,9,Fbeen imprisoned.
OL,11,F"They have lived in a very highly
OL,12,Fcontrolled or highly regulated
OL,13,Fenvironment. Some children when they
OL,14,Fcome into our refuges or our work,
OL,15,Fthey may still exhibit some of the
OL,16,Fthings that were expected of them by
OL,17,Fthe abuser."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/12
